                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15000858" author="srowen" created="Wed, 11 Nov 2015 18:27:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I may be missing some point, but Spark isn&apos;t consuming serialized data from untrusted sources in general, right? The risk here is way down the list of risks if untrusted sources are sending closures to your cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15003982" author="darabos" created="Fri, 13 Nov 2015 13:34:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; I may be missing some point, but Spark isn&apos;t consuming serialized data from untrusted sources in general, right? The risk here is way down the list of risks if untrusted sources are sending closures to your cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was thinking of seemingly harmless things like executor heartbeats and stuff like that. I&apos;ve never looked at how authentication is implemented. All communications on all ports are authenticated? If so, then I don&apos;t see any way to exploit this either. Sorry for the noise then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
